{
  "stem": "945.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And within a year after we left, we left about Pesach time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Within a year after we left, we were in Canada.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The-- the-- From Budapest, there was already organization, the UNRAA, and the Joint, and the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The further we went, the more it was organized to help us get out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then I remember finally getting to Italy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Italy, we were first in Milano.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then we went to another town, a city in Cremona.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In Cremona, we were about six months.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We heard that-- we wanted to go to Palestine, but the borders were closed and people couldn't make it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They wouldn't allow.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The British wouldn't allow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we heard of an opportunity to go to Canada, and we registered, my brother and I, to go to Canada.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were accepted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one day we were told to take the shots, and we were put on a boat called We left Genoa, and on the 22nd of March, 1948, we landed in Halifax, Nova Scotia.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From there, we went on to Montreal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from Montreal, we went to an area in Saskatchewan, which is called Hoffer, Saskatchewan-- which we understand-- understood at that time, there was some distant relative of ours that had lived on a farm colony.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's where we ended up, in Hoffer, Saskatchewan.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We worked with-- with those people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They weren't our relatives, but they were from the same general area as we were, and their name was Hoffer.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They treated us not like relatives, but they gave us work, paid us a minimum wage, helped maybe us getting our parents out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For that, I'm always going to be grateful to them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "To this day, we are still feel like kinship.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
